{
  "texts": [
    "The key metrics used for this evaluation are detailed below:",
    "Mean squared error (MSE) is a metric that computes the average of the squared differences between predicted (H i) and actual values (H i) (Wang et al. 2022).",
    "This method is particularly effective for data with a Gaussian distribution, as it disproportionately penalizes larger errors more than smaller ones, ensuring a focus on significant discrepancies.",
    "The Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE) is derived by taking the square root of the MSE.",
    "This calculation results in an error measure in the same units as the predicted outputs."
  ]
}